# Scripts to Rule Them All

This project follows [GitHub's normalized script pattern](https://github.com/github/scripts-to-rule-them-all). All developer lifecycle tasks are performed via scripts in `./script/`. Never suggest `npm run` scripts, Makefile targets, or ad-hoc commands as the primary interface — use or extend the standard scripts instead.

| Script | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `script/bootstrap` | Install all dependencies |
| `script/setup` | First-time setup or reset to initial state (calls bootstrap) |
| `script/update` | Update after a pull (calls bootstrap) |
| `script/server` | Start the application (calls update first) |
| `script/test` | Run the test suite; accepts an optional path argument |
| `script/cibuild` | CI entry point (calls test) |

Scripts are executable shell files with no extension. Each script:
- Uses `#!/bin/sh` and `set -e`
- Changes to the project root via `cd "$(dirname "$0")/.."` 
- Delegates to other scripts in the chain rather than duplicating logic
